		<div id="comment_body_64412342"><p><div class="quote"><p>If the US domestic industry can't compete, I'm inclined to say it deserves to die.</p> </div><p>The US auto industry competes just fine at building what Americans want to drive.  The challenge comes in switching over to building what the American government wants Americans to drive.  They are far from the same thing.
<br> <br>
If you had a successful company building something and then the government came along and said you must build something else - I'm not sure any company would not have difficulty with that.  Imagine HP being told they had to build cell phones instead of servers, or Glock being told they had to build tasers instead of guns, or Levis being told they have to make carpets instead of clothing, you get the idea.</p></div>
	</div>

